&lt;p&gt;In Java, arrays are passed by reference, however. In PHP they are considered as primitive types, which means if you have
an array with 5.000 elements and you pass it to a function, that array will be fully copied inside that function and any
modification won’t alter the original one.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
